"On E/Gb Lh plays Gb and R Hand plays E triad arpeggios"
"Gb lydian (i.e Db Major scale) on Fm7/Gb"
"First chorus - out of tempo - starts here"
"Bass descends chromatically over next 4 bars."
"Chord choice is more or less governed by the melody note at that point."
"Next four bars Root moves down in steps agin."
"Root again descends chromatically from Db"
"Bridge - another descending chromatic root  movement for the next 7 bars"
"Last 10 bars uses the usual chords"
"Return to Intro to finish 1st chorus"
"Bass and Drums in tempo"
"Bass and piano play contrapuntally"
"Piano Rh and LH in unison an Octave apart"
"RH and LH a tenth apart"
"Back to RH and LH an octave apart"
